 Reflection

One of the main challenges in this assignment was translating functional requirements into use cases.
While requirements describe what the system should do, use cases required a deeper understanding of how users interact with the system step-by-step.

Another challenge was ensuring that all stakeholders identified in Assignment 4 were properly represented in the use case diagram.
Balancing simplicity while including sufficient detail was also difficult.

Developing test cases required aligning each test with specific functional requirements. 
It was important to ensure that each test case clearly validated system behavior.

Additionally, defining non-functional test scenarios such as performance and security required careful thinking, 
as these are not directly visible features but are critical to system success.
Overall, this assignment improved understanding of system modeling, user interaction, and validation processes in software engineering.
